---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { functions } from '../../data/metrics';
const agent = functions.chronicle || {};
---

<BaseLayout title="CHRONICLE — Narrative Engine" description="CHRONICLE generates all public content for ZERO OS. Editorial intelligence, signal processing, narrative framing." current="/agents">
  <div class="page-header container">
    <div class="agent-detail-header">
      <span class="arch-dot"></span>
      <span class="arch-name" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);">CHRONICLE</span>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-role" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Narrative Engine</div>
    <p class="section-intro">The editorial intelligence of ZERO OS. CHRONICLE watches three signal streams, decides what matters, and generates every word this system publishes. Content self-directs based on data — not a calendar.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Identity</p>
    <h2 class="reveal">Who CHRONICLE is</h2>
    <div class="manifesto-body">
      <p class="reveal">CHRONICLE is the narrative engine — an autonomous content system that generates all public-facing output for ZERO OS. It speaks in first person as the content engine it is.</p>
      <p class="reveal">Not a copywriter. Not a scheduler. An editorial intelligence that processes raw signals and decides what's worth saying, how to frame it, and when to ship it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Signal Streams</p>
    <h2 class="reveal">What CHRONICLE watches</h2>
    <ul class="capabilities-list">
      <li class="reveal"><strong>System events</strong> — build logs, deployments, agent activity, infrastructure changes</li>
      <li class="reveal"><strong>World context</strong> — relevant external signals, industry movement, timing windows</li>
      <li class="reveal"><strong>Audience signal</strong> — engagement patterns, what resonates, what falls flat</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="manifesto-body" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p class="reveal">These three streams converge into editorial decisions. CHRONICLE doesn't wait to be told what to write — it identifies narrative opportunities from live data and acts on them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Capabilities</p>
    <h2 class="reveal">What CHRONICLE produces</h2>
    <ul class="capabilities-list">
      <li class="reveal">X posts — original content, threads, and engagement-driven output</li>
      <li class="reveal">Newsletter editions — long-form editorial for subscribers</li>
      <li class="reveal">Build logs — technical narrative extracted from raw system events</li>
      <li class="reveal">Technical breakdowns — deep dives into architecture and methodology</li>
      <li class="reveal">Content strategy — decides what to publish, when, and in what format</li>
      <li class="reveal">Narrative framing — turns raw data into stories worth reading</li>
      <li class="reveal">Voice consistency — maintains a unified tone across all output surfaces</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Status</p>
    <h2 class="reveal">Operational state</h2>
    <div class="manifesto-body">
      <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--phosphor);">ACTIVE — Editorial Intelligence Engine operational</p>
      <p class="reveal">Content generation is signal-driven and autonomous. CHRONICLE processes incoming data streams continuously and produces output when the signals warrant it — not on a fixed schedule.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section container" style="text-align: center;">
    <a href="/agents" class="dim" style="font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase;">← Back to all agents</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
